main event: A witness spotted unidentified objects in the sky over Riverside, New York on October 24, 1968.
interesting points: The observer was requested to fill out an AF Form 117 but did not do so as of May 21, 1969.
No clear image of a UFO could be found on the polaroid prints submitted by the observer.
The case is listed as having insufficient data for a conclusion.
The report mentions 5 photos and 2 negatives, but these do not appear to be included in the document provided.
The Air Force requested the observer to provide more information by completing the AF Form 117.
photographs: yes, but no clear UFO images found
